---
const points = [
  {
    title: "Pre-auth filed with the right documentation.",
    body: "Know what each insurer requires for each procedure before you file. Fewer first denials mean more procedures that actually happen — and a schedule that holds.",
  },
  {
    title: "Authorization gaps surface early.",
    body: "Know which procedures are at risk before they fall off your schedule. Act before the revenue is already gone — not after the slot is empty.",
  },
  {
    title: "Denial triggers the appeal automatically.",
    body: "When authorization fails, the appeal process starts immediately — no delay, no manual trigger, no procedure lost to an administrative lag or a missed window.",
  },
  {
    title: "Procedure-level reimbursement intelligence.",
    body: "Know what you're actually getting per procedure per insurer — and where your appeal effort has the highest return. Not instinct. Data.",
  },
  {
    title: "Expert review stays in control.",
    body: "Every generated letter and argument is reviewed before submission. ClearIQ handles the preparation. Your team handles the judgment. Nothing goes out without human sign-off.",
  },
];
---

<section class="notai">
  <div class="container notai-inner">
    <div class="notai-left">
      <span class="section-label section-label--white">What ClearIQ Is</span>
      <h2 class="notai-headline">
        The revenue problem<br />
        isn't the appeal.<br />
        <em>It's everything before it.</em>
      </h2>
      <p class="notai-body">
        Generic tools generate text. ClearIQ manages the authorization pipeline.
        A denied procedure is not primarily an appeal problem — it is a
        pre-certification, documentation, and insurer-intelligence problem.
        The right information, filed with the right payer-specific language, is what
        prevents the denial. When prevention fails, ClearIQ automates the recovery.
        That is the full scope of the problem this platform is built to solve.
      </p>
      <a href="#early-access" class="btn btn-primary notai-cta">
        Join the Waitlist
        <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M3 8h10M9 4l4 4-4 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
        </svg>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="notai-right">
      {points.map((p) => (
        <article class="notai-point">
          <div class="notai-point-check" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 14 14" fill="none">
              <path d="M2.5 7l3 3 6-6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="notai-point-title">{p.title}</h3>
            <p class="notai-point-body">{p.body}</p>
          </div>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .notai {
    background: var(--navy-mid);
    padding: var(--section-y) 0;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .notai::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background-image:
      linear-gradient(rgba(26,142,168,0.04) 1px, transparent 1px),
      linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(26,142,168,0.04) 1px, transparent 1px);
    background-size: 48px 48px;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .notai-inner {
    position: relative;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 80px;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .notai-headline {
    font-size: clamp(1.7rem, 3vw, 2.4rem);
    color: var(--white);
    margin-bottom: 22px;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .notai-body {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.60);
    line-height: 1.78;
    margin-bottom: 36px;
  }

  .notai-cta {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .notai-right {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 28px;
    padding-top: 8px;
  }

  .notai-point {
    display: flex;
    gap: 16px;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .notai-point-check {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 28px;
    height: 28px;
    background: rgba(26,142,168,0.18);
    border: 1px solid rgba(26,142,168,0.30);
    border-radius: 50%;
    color: var(--teal);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 2px;
  }

  .notai-point-title {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--white);
    margin-bottom: 6px;
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
  }

  .notai-point-body {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.55);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  @media (max-width: 840px) {
    .notai-inner {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 48px;
    }
  }
</style>
